  <title>What are the color codes of the Part Editor?</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>FAQ<keyword>Colors used in the Part Editor?</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">What are the color codes of the Part-Editor?</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Color-codes of Elements in the Part-Editor</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You can edit the Color for the two states of Geometry. </para>
    <list id="29" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Geometry Under Defined</li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Geometry Fully Defined.</li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_2" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:60px;"><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif"><caption><![CDATA[Sketch-Elements: Not Fully-Defined and Fully-Defined: Blue and Black]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:206px;">
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><image src="PG-ColourCode1.bmp" align="left" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title>Not fully defined sketch in Part Editor</title></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">There are two colors that we use to identify sketch-elements that are <text styleclass="VariableName">not fully-defined</text> and <text styleclass="VariableName">fully-defined.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">The colors depend on the theme you are using.</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Not Fully-Defined (= Under-Defined)</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#0000ff;">Color: typically Blue</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You will notice that as you add sketch-elements in the <text styleclass="Element">Part-Editor</text> they are <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#0000ff;">Blue</text><text style="font-weight:bold; color:#0000ff;">&#32;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">This is the color of <text styleclass="VariableName">under-defined geometry</text>. You will find that you can still drag <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#0000ff;">Blue</text> sketch-elements.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:206px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="PG-ColourCode2.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title>Fully Defined Sketch in Part Editor</title></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Fully-Defined</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Color: typically Black</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Ideally, you should add dimension and constraints to your sketch so that all the sketch-elements are <text styleclass="VariableName">Black</text>. This means the sketch is fully-defined. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">There is no correct or incorrect way to define the sketch-elements. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Dimensions and Constraints should agree with the design intent.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_2" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:60px;"><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif" src-print="none"><caption><![CDATA[Reference Geometry, Sketch-Elements from Other Mechanisms, Dimensions in a Design-Set]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:235px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="RefGeometry-PartEditor.bmp" align="left" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title>Reference Geometry</title></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Reference Geometry</text> is <text style="font-weight:bold; color:#ff8000;">Orange</text><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Other <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editors</text> are <text style="font-weight:bold; color:#787771;">Gray</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image> when <text styleclass="T_Menu">Show other Kinematic and Sketch elements</text> tool is active.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:235px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="Dimensions-Design-Set.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Dimensions are used to control an element, they are <text style="font-weight:bold; color:#787771;">Gray</text>&#32;</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">For example:</para>
          <list id="30" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text style="font-weight:normal; color:#000000;">Dimension of a </text><text styleclass="Element">Line</text><text style="font-weight:normal; color:#000000;"> that is the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Gears-Line-of-Centres" style="font-weight:normal; color:#000000;">Line-between-centers</link></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:normal; color:#000000;">Dimension of an </text><text styleclass="Element">Arc</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:normal; color:#000000;"> for a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Mechanism-Pulley" styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:normal; color:#000000;">Pulley</link></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Dimensions added to <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-FB-DesignSet">Design-Sets</link></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Dimension controlled with a Parameter-Control.</li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
